byline.contributor: Elian Peltier and Nabih Bulos contributed reporting.

abstract: Parisians are slowly coming to terms with fact that attack by Islamic State supporters on November 13 is not likely to be last of its kind in their city.
lead_paragraph: The city wants to get past the lost tourism and uncertainties that followed the Nov. 13 attacks. But as candles burn low and bouquets wilt, a certain shock lingers.

headline.main: Paris Slowly Coming to Terms With a New Vulnerability
headline.print_headline: Parisians Are Slowly Coming to Terms With Their New Sense of Vulnerability
